Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay fine light brown; some mica; small white inclusions. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 201, 39? An example from Kalonero, Thasos is from a context of c.370-250BC, more likely earlier than later (Y. Garlan in Recherches sur les amphores grecques [BCH Suppl. XIII], 248 and 266).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1587)
